      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, it sounds like your product image is being a bit of a mischievous goblin, hiding behind the title text on mobile screens. This could be due to a few reasons, like the image not scaling down properly or the title text not adjusting its position to accommodate the image. Let's try to tame this goblin with some CSS magic:\n\n```css\n@media (max-width: 768px) {\n  .product-header {\n    flex-direction: row;\n    align-items: center;\n  }\n\n  .product-image-wrapper {\n    margin-bottom: 10px;\n  }\n\n  .product-info {\n    padding: 10px;\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThis snippet should help your product image and title text to live in harmony, even on smaller screens. The `@media` rule ensures that when the screen size is 768px or smaller, the layout changes to a row, with the image and title text aligned in the center. The additional margin and padding adjustments should help prevent the image from overlapping the title text. Give it a try and see if your shop's goblins are put to good use!",
